{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-template-tsx","path":"/blog/adding-slide-numbers-to-mdx-deck-presentations/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"8c3a5c6a-46bb-5a74-9ead-d81b55dd54ed","excerpt":"MDX Deck is a fast and lightweight library that lets you write presentations in markdown. More specifically, it uses MDX, an extension of markdown that allowsâ€¦","html":"<p>MDX Deck is a fast and lightweight library that lets you write presentations in markdown. More specifically, it uses <a href=\"https://github.com/mdx-js/mdx\">MDX</a>, an extension of markdown that allows you to use JSX and React components. This allows you to do cool things like import React components into your slide deck and interact with them.</p>\n<p>First, follow the <a href=\"https://github.com/jxnblk/mdx-deck#getting-started\">Getting Started</a> instructions in the README of MDX Deck.</p>\n<p>You should end up with the following file structure:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"md\"><pre class=\"language-md\"><code class=\"language-md\">.\nâ”œâ”€â”€ node_modules\nâ”œâ”€â”€ deck.mdx\nâ”œâ”€â”€ README.md\nâ”œâ”€â”€ package.json\nâ”œâ”€â”€ package-lock.lock</code></pre></div>\n<p>Then create a <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Layout&gt;</code> component:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token comment\">// layout.js</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">Layout</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> children <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>children<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>footer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">My Awesome Presentation! ðŸš€</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">@corrinachow</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>footer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n    </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Layout<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>You can now create slides in your <code class=\"language-text\">deck.mdx</code> file with the <code class=\"language-text\">Layout</code> component where the slide contents will render as <code class=\"language-text\">children</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"md\"><pre class=\"language-md\"><code class=\"language-md\">// deck.mdx\n\nimport Layout from \"./Layout\";\n\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>Layout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token title important\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">#</span> My Awesome Presentation!</span>\n  ðŸš€ Corrina Chow\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>Layout</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>;</code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/nlkh0fenwngqd1xj6dud.png\" alt=\"MDX presentation with footer\"></p>\n<figcaption>MDX Deck slide with footer using a Layout component</figcaption>\n<p>This is useful for making headers, footers or layouts for your slides.</p>\n<p>Now if you dig into the source code, you'll see that MDX Deck uses a React Context called <code class=\"language-text\">useDeck</code> to pass deck data between components. This includes the index of the slide, speaker notes, or presentation mode!</p>\n<p>This hook happens to be exported from the library and can be used to your advange.</p>\n<p>In <code class=\"language-text\">layout.js</code> file, import the <code class=\"language-text\">useDeck</code> React hook from <code class=\"language-text\">mdx-deck</code>. There's a property represents index of the slide you're viewing. From that, you're able to extract slide numbers and add it to your presentation ðŸ¥³</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"language-jsx\"><code class=\"language-jsx\"><span class=\"token comment\">// layout.js</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"react\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> useDeck <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"mdx-deck\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Import useDeck</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">Layout</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> children <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> state <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token function\">useDeck</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// Declare a new state variable</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> currentSlide <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> state<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>index <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// The slides are zero-index</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>children<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>footer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">My Awesome Presentation! ðŸš€</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>currentSlide<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n        </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">@corrinachow</span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>span</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n      </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>footer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span><span class=\"token plain-text\">\n    </span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> Layout<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/xg2hmzcxqnkj7mm775r4.png\" alt=\"MDX Deck with slide number\"></p>\n<figcaption>MDX Deck with slide number!</figcaption>\n<p>There's a bunch of other values that can be accessed with the <code class=\"language-text\">useDeck</code> context, such as the <code class=\"language-text\">length</code> of the presentation, or HTML <code class=\"language-text\">head</code> values.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/i/cdvqlvxqqnggdemh97gc.png\" alt=\"useDeck props\"></p>\n<figcaption>useDeck properties</figcaption>\n<p>Hope this was helpful ðŸ˜„</p>\n<h2 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>References</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://reactjs.org/docs/context.html\">React Context</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mdx-js/mdx\">MDX Docs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jxnblk/mdx-deck\">MDX Deck</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Adding Slide Numbers to MDX Deck Presentations","date":"July 26, 2020","description":"A tutorial on how to add slide numbers to MDX deck presentation."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/adding-slide-numbers-to-mdx-deck-presentations/"}}}